``` 

This proof uses the fact that two linear solutions are equal if their underlying charges are equal (`LinSols.ext_iff`). The `simp_all` tactic simplifies the hypothesis `h` to `x.val = y.val`, and then `aesop` can directly conclude `x = y` because `x.val = y.val` implies all components of the solutions are equal. This is a straightforward proof that does not require additional lemmas or theorems beyond the structure of `LinSols`.
